        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "BGE M3 often delivers lower latency and cost, making it suitable for high-throughput APIs, though OpenAI's model may offer broader ecosystem support."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "API Integration and Configuration"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Integrating BGE M3 into your API stack requires minimal setup. Use the Hugging Face Transformers library with FP16 precision for optimal performance. Example Python snippet for generating embeddings:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code_block",
        "lang": "python",
        "value": "from transformers import AutoTokenizer, AutoModel\nimport torch\n\ntokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained('BAAI/bge-m3')\nmodel = AutoModel.from_pretrained('BAAI/bge-m3', torch_dtype=torch.float16)\n\ndef get_embedding(text):\n    inputs = tokenizer(text, return_tensors='pt', padding=True, truncation=True)\n    with torch.no_grad():\n        outputs = model(**inputs)\n    return outputs.last_hidden_state.mean(dim=1).numpy()",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "from transformers import AutoTokenizer, AutoModel"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "import torch"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": ""
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained('BAAI/bge-m3')"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "model = AutoModel.from_pretrained('BAAI/bge-m3', torch_dtype=torch.float16)"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": ""
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "def get_embedding(text):"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "    inputs = tokenizer(text, return_tensors='pt', padding=True, truncation=True)"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "    with torch.no_grad():"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "        outputs = model(**inputs)"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "    return outputs.last_hidden_state.mean(dim=1).numpy()"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For OpenAI, use their API client, but note that BGE M3 can be self-hosted, reducing external dependencies and latency."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cost Analysis and Scalability"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "BGE M3's self-hosted nature allows for predictable cost scaling. On a GPU instance (e.g., NVIDIA T4), it handles ~1000 requests/sec at a fraction of OpenAI's per-token pricing. For large-scale APIs, this translates to significant savings. However, factor in infrastructure management overhead compared to OpenAI's managed service."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Production Deployment Best Practices"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Deploy BGE M3 with containerization (e.g., Docker) and orchestration tools like Kubernetes for resilience. Monitor key metrics: latency, error rates, and GPU utilization. Implement caching for frequent queries to reduce load. For hybrid approaches, consider using BGE M3 for high-volume tasks and OpenAI for fallback or specific use cases requiring higher dimensions."
          }
        ]
      }
